Ragi Gingerbread Cake with Cream Cheese Frosting 🎄

#AD

📝 Ingredients:
20g ghee
30g raw cane sugar
80ml milk
40g molasses or date syrup
40g curd/yogurt
1/2tsp vanilla extract
50g ragi
50g all purpose flour
1/2tsp ground ginger
1/2tsp cinnamon 
1/2tsp cardamom
1tsp baking powder
1/4tsp baking soda

Recipe
- In a bowl, mix together melted ghee, raw sugar, milk, molasses, curd and vanilla extract. Mix well. 
- Sift in the ragi and all purpose flour along with ground ginger, cinnamon, cardamom, salt, baking powder and baking soda. Using a spatula, fold gently. 
- In a 6 inch tin lined with parchment paper, bake at 180C in a preheated oven for about 25-30 minutes. 

📝 Ingredients for Cream Cheese Frosting:
- 100g cream cheese at room temperature
- 50g salted butter at room temperature
- 125-150g powdered sugar (adjust as per liking)
- 1tsp vanilla extract

Recipe:
- Beat the cream cheese and butter together on high speed until smooth and creamy. 
- Add the sugar and vanilla. Beat the mixture some more till fluffy and stable. 

I highly recommend this cake with the frosting but tbh, it works great as a Tea Cake as well. You choose what works for you🥰

Say hello to Kodo Millet Milk! 🌿 A nutritious, plant-based milk alternative that’s easy to make and packed with health benefits. Perfect for smoothies, cereals, coffee, or even enjoyed on its own, this wholesome superfood is here to take your wellness game up a notch! 💪🏼✨ 

Why Kodo Millet Milk?

✅ Naturally gluten-free & gut-friendly
✅ Rich in fiber, vitamins, and minerals
✅ Boosts energy and supports heart health
✅ A sustainable and wholesome alternative to dairy

Tips for Smooth & Delicious Millet Milk:

1️⃣ Soak the Millet: Soak for 6-8 hours (or overnight) to soften the grains. This makes blending easier and results in creamier milk while removing any bitterness.
2️⃣ Perfect Ratio: Use 1 cup of soaked millet to 3-4 cups of water, depending on your desired thickness.
3️⃣ Flavor It Up: Add natural sweeteners like dates, honey, or jaggery, and flavorings such as vanilla extract or a pinch of cinnamon for extra taste.
4️⃣ Store Properly: Keep it in an airtight container in the fridge for up to 4-5 days. Shake before use as separation is natural.
5️⃣ Don’t Waste the Pulp: Use the leftover millet pulp in smoothies, baking, or oatmeal for added nutrition.

Give your body the goodness it deserves—one sip at a time! 🌱

✨ Broccoli Cheese Paratha ✨

Broccoli Cheese Paratha is a delicious, nutritious, and flavorful Indian flatbread stuffed with a blend of grated broccoli and melted cheese. This fusion dish is perfect for breakfast, lunch, or dinner, offering a healthy twist to the traditional paratha while keeping it indulgent with the cheesy filling. It’s a great way to sneak in veggies for kids and adults alike!

Ingredients:
For the filling:

1 ½ cups finely grated broccoli (about 1 small broccoli)
1 cup grated cheese (Processed , cheddar, or a blend)
1 tbsp finely chopped coriander (optional)
1 small green chili, finely chopped (optional)
1 teaspoon Red chilli flakes 
Salt to taste
1 tbsp oil or Ghee for cooking

For the dough:

1 ½ cups Raagi flour
¼ tsp salt
½ tsp ajwain (carom seeds) (optional)
Water (as needed to knead the dough)
1 tbsp Ghee
